import requests
response = requests.get("https://www.menuism.com/restaurant-locations/starbucks-coffee-39564")


from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, "html.parser")
starbs = soup.find_all("li", attrs={
                      "class": ""})
starbs
[]
rows = []

for locations in soup.find_all("li", class_=""): # what does the word before for mean
  link_text = locations.get_text()
  state_name = link_text.split("Starbucks Coffee Locations")[0].strip()
  rows.append(state_name)
rows
states_stores = rows[17:68] # select state rows
string = ", ".join(states_stores) # join together to form one long string
one_p = string.replace(")"," ") # remove parentheses
sec_p = one_p.replace("("," ")
no_locations = sec_p.replace("Starbucks Coffee locations", "").strip() # remove Starbucks Coffee locations

#chatgpt
state_info = no_locations.split(" , ")
state_names = []
state_counts = []

for pair in state_info:
    name, count = pair.split('   ')
    state_names.append(name)
    state_counts.append(int(count))

df = pd.DataFrame({
    'State Name': state_names,
    'State Count': state_counts
})

df

# starbucks

response_starbucks = requests.get("https://www.menuism.com/restaurant-locations/starbucks-coffee-39564")

soup_star = BeautifulSoup(response_starbucks.content, "html.parser")

# Finding All US Stores
stores_star = soup_star.find_all("li",
attrs={"class": ""})

# Creating For Loop that Goes Through Each Store
rows_starbucks = []

for store in stores_star:

# Adjusting for Content not containing Titles or Relevant Keys
  if store.find("a") != None:
    cells = store.find("a")

  if cells.get('title') != None:
    loc_tag = cells.get('title')

# Filtering Just to US Locations
  if loc_tag[-2:] == "us" and loc_tag[-6:-4] != "dc":

# Find the name of the State
                store_tag = cells.get_text()

# Creating List of Store Tag to Obtain State Name
                tag_list = store_tag.split(" ")

                states_list = ['Dakota','Carolina','Hampshire','York','Jersey','Mexico','Island','Virginia']
                if tag_list[1] not in states_list:
                    state_name = tag_list[0]

                else:
                    state_name = " ".join(tag_list[0:2])

                store_locations = re.findall(r'\((.*?)\)', store_tag)[0] # Locations In Between Parentheses
  store_locations = pd.to_numeric(store_locations) # Converting to Integers

# Obtaining Store Name from URL
pattern = r'/([^/]+)$'
store_name = re.findall(pattern, url_dd)[0]
# Append this data.
rows_starbucks.append({
                    "State": state_name,
                    store_name:store_locations
                })

# Converting Rows to Dataframe
starbucks_df = pd.DataFrame(rows_starbucks)
# Confirming Webscraping Worked
starbucks_df.head()

def stateabbr(state):
    """
    Outputs the state abbreviation when given the state full name
    case insensitive and spelling doesn't matter

    Parameter
    ---------
    state : str
    A string of the state name

    Returns
    -------
    str
    A string of the state abbreviation

    """
    state_name = us.states.lookup(state)
    if state_name is not None:
        return state_name.abbr
    else:
        return "State not found"

Automate

def coffee_shop(url):
    """
    Produce a clean, orgnaized dataset that has 3 columns: state abbreviation, location count, and company name after given a website to scrape from.

    Parameter
    ---------
    url: str
    The url link of the website to be scraped

    Returns
    -------
    Pandas dataframe
    Includes state abbreviation, location count, and company name.

    """
    response_shop = requests.get(url)

    soup_shop = BeautifulSoup(response_shop.content, "html.parser")

    # Finding All US Stores
    stores_shop = soup_shop.find_all("li",
                            attrs=
                             {"class": ""})

    # Creating For Loop that Goes Through Each Store
    rows_shop = []

    for store in stores_shop:

        # Adjusting for Content not containing Titles or Relevant Keys
        if store.find("a") != None:
            cells = store.find("a")

            if cells.get('title') != None:
                loc_tag = cells.get('title')

                # Filtering Just to US Locations
                if loc_tag[-2:] == "us" and loc_tag[-6:-4] != "dc":

                  # Find the name of the State
                    store_tag = cells.get_text()

                  # Creating List of Store Tag to Obtain State Name
                    tag_list = store_tag.split(" ")

                    states_list = ['Dakota','Carolina','Hampshire','York','Jersey','Mexico','Island','Virginia']
                    if tag_list[1] not in states_list:
                        state_name = tag_list[0]

                    else:
                        state_name = " ".join(tag_list[0:2])

                    store_locations = re.findall(r'\((.*?)\)', store_tag)[0] # Locations In Between Parentheses
                    store_locations = pd.to_numeric(store_locations) # Converting to Integers

                  # Obtaining Store Name from URL
                    pattern = r'/([^/]+)$'
                    store_name = re.findall(pattern, url_dd)[0]

                  # Append this data.
                    rows_shop.append({
                        "State": state_name,
                        store_name:store_locations
                    })

    # Converting Rows to Dataframe
    shop_df = pd.DataFrame(rows_shop)

    #apply abbreviation function to get state abbreviations
    shop_state_df = shop_df.apply(lambda x: stateabbr(x["State"]), axis=1)

    return shop_state_df
